  NEW AT CONSORTIUMINFO.ORG </em></strong></font></em></strong></p>
              <p align="left"> <span class="style2">With this issue, you will notice some of the new features that we&rsquo;ve recently added to the <strong><em>Consortium Standards Bulletin</em></strong>: you can now print a single article from the <strong><em>CSB</em></strong> or the entire issue in a properly formatted Word/pdf version. Over the next month, we will be converting each article in the preceding 13 issues of the <strong><em>CSB</em></strong> to the same format and print availability &ndash; more than 50 articles in all. </span></p>
              <p align="left" class="style2"> We have also created a convenient title and abstract index of all articles to date, with links that will take you to entire issues, or individual articles. You can find the new index <a href="/bulletins/">here</a>. </p>
              <p align="left" class="style2"> We are also in the process of expanding the Consortium and Standards List, which is already the most complete index on the Internet of consortia, accredited standards bodies and related resources, with over 300 organizations listed. For each listing, we provide an overview of the SSO and its mission, as well as links to its site, and, if a password is not required, its specifications and intellectual roperty rights policy as well. You can find the complete list at <a href="/links/">http://www.consortiuminfo.org/links/</a></p>
              <p align="left" class="style2"> Please know that we always welcome contributions of articles, press releases and links to other appropriate sites. Here&rsquo;s how you can help: </p>
              <div align="left">
                <ul>
                    <li class="style2"><strong><em> If your organization is not already listed</em></strong> in the Consortium and Standards List, please submit the required information at <a href="/suggest/">http://www.consortiuminfo.org/suggest/ </a></li>
                </ul>
                <ul>
                    <li class="style2"><strong><em> If you are not already sending your press releases</em></strong> to us for inclusion at the News Section &lt; <a href="/news/">http://www.consortiuminfo.org/news/</a>&gt; of our site and in the <strong><em>CSB,</em></strong> please add <script language="javascript" type="text/javascript">NewsConAdd();</script> to your press release distribution list </li>
                </ul>
                <ul>
                    <li class="style2"><strong><em> If you have an article on standards or standard setting</em></strong> that you would like us to abstract and either host or link at the Articles and Resources &lt; <a href="/articles/">http://www.consortiuminfo.org/articles/</a>&gt; section of our site, please submit it at <a href="/submit/ui/">ttp://www.consortiuminfo.org/submit/ui/ </a></li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <p align="left" class="style2"> Finally, we welcome you to link your site to ours. Linking information can be found at: <a href="/link/">http://www.consortiuminfo.org/link/</a> If you have other suggestions on how we can work together, please contact <a href="<em>Comments? </em> Email: <script language="javascript" type="text/javascript">AuConAdd();</script>">Updegrove@consortiuminfo.org</a></p>
              <p align="left" class="style2"><a href="/subscribe/"><img src="/images/subscribe-csb.gif" width="130" height="25" border="0"></a> </p>
